
	c operator:
	===========
	
		def: operator is a symbol.(+ - ++ * / > < .....)	
		     it is used to perform some operations ex: arithmetic,relational,..


	1) Arithmetic operator
		+	addition
		-	subtraction
		*	mulitiplication
		/	division (quotient )
		%	modules (remainder value )


	2) Relational operator
	
		<
		<=
		>
		>=
		==
		!=
	
	3) logical operator
	
		&& 	logical and
		||	logical or
		!	logical not

	4) assignment operator

		=
		+=
		-=
		*=
		/=
		%=
	5) increment/decrement operator

		++  (increment operator)	
		--  (decrement operator)

		two types:
			
			pre increment/decrement ex: ++a; --a;

			post increment/decrement: ex: a++; a--;

	6) conditional operator
			
			exp1? exp2 : exp3;

		expresson:
			a
			a<b
			a>=b
			a>b?a:b;

			int a=10,b=20;
			ans=a>b?a:b;	

	7) bitwise operator

		&	bitwise and
		|	bitwise or
		<<	left shift
		>> 	right shift	
	
			
	
